gate: OPEN
task: S75-TB2
title: Sync Locale from Server Settings on Login
description: |
  Currently the app uses browser language detection (i18next-browser-languagedetector)
  but the server stores the user's preferred locale in Settings.locale.
  After login the app should apply the server locale preference.

  Steps:
    1. In the login success flow (App.tsx or wherever fetchVehicles/post-login
       bootstrap happens), add a call to useSettingsStore.fetchSettings() if not
       already happening post-login.

    2. After fetchSettings() resolves, read settings.locale:
         const locale = settingsStore.getState().settings?.locale
         if (locale && ['en', 'uk', 'ru'].includes(locale)) {
           i18n.changeLanguage(locale)
           localStorage.setItem('i18nextLng', locale)
         }

    3. Direction of sync on change:
       - User changes language in app → updateSetting({ locale: code }) sends to server ✓ (already in language-selector)
       - Server → app: on login only (see step 2 above).

    4. Verify: log in as user with locale='ru' set on server → app switches to Russian
       without requiring manual language selection.

  Note: Do NOT call fetchSettings() on every vehicle refresh cycle.
  It should only be called once on login / app bootstrap.

acceptance:
  - Logging in with a server-side locale='ru' → app displays Russian
  - Logging in with locale='uk' → app displays Ukrainian
  - Language change in app settings updates server locale via updateSetting()
  - fetchSettings() is called once at login, not on every poll cycle

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
estimated: 1 hour
dep: S75-TA1
